Dusan Vlahovic insists he knew what he was taking on when he assumed Cristiano Ronaldo’s No 7 shirt at Juventus. The Serbian forward, linked with Arsenal for much of January, made a recent switch from Fiorentina to the Old Lady. Vlahovic enjoyed a phenomenal 2021, equalling Ronaldo’s Serie A record for goals in a calendar year. Man Utd Release Statement After Mason Greenwood Further Arrested… Osimhen To Miss Crucial World Cup Play-off Against Ghana It caught the attention of several clubs around Europe but it was Juventus who won the race for his signature. The Italian side allowed Ronaldo to depart for Manchester United in the summer, leaving a sizeable void in their squad. Vlahovic’s arrival will go someway to plugging that and the forward had no reservations about taking on the No 7.